text: FJ may refer to: == Places == * Fiji (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code) ** .fj, the country code top level domain (ccTLD) for Fiji ** Fijian language (ISO 639-1 language code) * Fujian, a province of China == Vehicles == * FJ Fury, an early Cold War fighter aircraft of the US Navy * Flying Junior, a sailing dinghy * Toyota FJ Cruiser, a sport utility vehicle * Holden FJ, an Australian car * Yamaha FJ, motorcycle == Other uses == * Fallschirmjäger, German paratroopers * The FASEB Journal, a scientific journal of experimental biosciences * Femtojoule (fJ), an SI unit of energy equal to 10−15 joules * Fiji Airways (IATA code) * Formula Junior, an auto racing class ==See also== *FJS (disambiguation)
title: FJ
